03/02/2004
ROME, Italy -- Albanian Foreign Minister Kastriot Islami and Italian Interior Minister Giuseppe Pisanu met on Monday (2 February) to discuss measures against organised crime.
Afterwards, they announced a commitment to joint efforts in fighting human, drugs and arms trafficking.
The two countries will also work to strengthen border security.
In other news Monday, Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano met with European Investment Bank (EIB) Vice-President Gerlando Genuardi.
They discussed progress in implementing EIB-backed projects in Albania and possible new investments in the country.
(ATA - 02/02/04)
